THE grave of a woman in Hekpoort, Gauteng, was violated on Saturday. Constable Gloria Maswanganye said they were investigating. “The owner of a farm in Hartebeesfontein claimed he went to the cemetery on his farm and found a dug-up grave,” she said. “The grave was that of a woman born in 1907 and buried in 1974.” She told Daily Sun the man also found some of the remains lying on the soil. Maswanganye said the headstone at another grave was damaged. “We will do our best to find the culprits,” she said. She said the motive was unknown and encouraged people around Hekpoort to visit their loved ones’ graves to check if they are still in good condition. “If violated, immediately call the police.”